bilingual.target: 城市的人口正在迅速增长。
城市的景观在不断变化。

bilingual.source: Urban areas tend to have better access to healthcare.
bilingual.target: 城市的地区通常有更好的医疗服务。

bilingual.source: The urban environ can be quite stressful for some people.
bilingual.target: 城市的环境对一些人来说可能相当有压力。

bilingual.source: Rapid urban intensification has led to traffic congestion.
bilingual.target: 城市的快速集约化导致了交通拥堵。

bilingual.source: The government is investing in urban development projects.
bilingual.target: 政府正在投资城市的发展项目。

bilingual.source: Many young people prefer urban living for its convenience.
bilingual.target: 许多年轻人喜欢城市的生活，因为它方便。

bilingual.source: Multimodal transportation systems can reduce urban traffic congestion.
bilingual.target: 多模态交通系统可以减少城市的交通拥堵。

bilingual.source: Her depictions of urban life capture the essence of the city.
bilingual.target: 她对城市生活的描绘抓住了城市的精髓。

bilingual.source: The urban soundscape is filled with the noise of traffic and construction.
bilingual.target: 城市的声景充满了交通和施工的噪音。

list.abstract: Urban都市音乐，又称为Urban Contemporary，是二十世纪八十年代和九十年代基于R&B/Soul出现的新词。
Urban（英[ˈɜːbən]，美[ˈɜːrbən]），英语单词，形容词，城市的；与城市有关的；有城市特色的。短语搭配为urban planning（城市规划）。例句为“The enviable urban lifestyle in Britain.（英国令人羡慕的城市生活方式。）” 其形容词性近义词为city，反义词为rural；名词性同根词urbanization，释义为都市化；文雅化。

yingyinNormal.en: This urban transformation is spread across China.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这种城市化进程遍及整个中国。

yingyinNormal.en: Despite Singapore's high urban density, the island is incredibly fertile.
yingyinNormal.zh: 虽然新加坡是个人口稠密的都市，岛上土地却十分肥沃。

yingyinNormal.en: Fine. In the parlance of the urban music scene, "what's the 4-1-1"?
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，用城市音乐[黑人音乐]的术语来说"你想跟我说啥"？

yingyinNormal.en: Now it's time to use a darker base. This is URBAN DECAY's ROCKSTAR.
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在要用深色的粉底。这个是URBAN DECAY的旗舰产品。

yingyinNormal.en: Or a, hookup as it's referred to by today's urban youth. Really? Yes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 或者说，配对，现在的都市青年好像都这么说的。真的吗？是的。

yingyinNormal.en: So let's zoom into eye makeup stuff. I first used Urban Decay Eye Primer Potion.
yingyinNormal.zh: 下面来看看眼部妆容化妆品。我最先使用的是Urban Decay眼部妆容打底霜。

yingyinNormal.en: While closer to earth, Hong Kong's urban centers feature pockets of peace everywhere.
yingyinNormal.zh: 虽然人烟稠密，但香港市区到处都很安全。

yingyinNormal.en: Just a short ferry ride from Luna Park is Darling Harbor, one of Sydney's urban renewal triumphs.
yingyinNormal.zh: 从月神公园乘坐渡轮，很快便来到达令港，这是悉尼市区重建的杰出地区之一。

yingyinNormal.en: An area composed of more than 250 islands, the urban core of Hong Kong is Hong Kong Island and Kowloon.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这片区域由250多个岛屿组成，香港的市中心是香港岛和九龙。

yingyinNormal.en: That's the last thing we need. The president in the middle of an urban battle. Or the citizens of London.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们最不希望看到的就是总统深陷城市战火中。还有伦敦的市民们。

yingyinNormal.en: The manpower required to drive this urban explosion has come from the rural backwaters of this vast nation.
yingyinNormal.zh: 驱动城市扩张所需的人力来自于辽阔中国的农村落后地区。

yingyinNormal.en: For the new urban middle class, the summer brings a new western-style holiday into their calendar: the beach holiday.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对于都市新晋中产阶级来说，炎炎夏日带来了一个新的西方风格的节日：海滨度假日。

yingyinNormal.en: Our car culture is so common now that we forget how different it is from the rhythms of urban American life just a half century ago.
yingyinNormal.zh: 随着汽车文化的普及，我们已经忘记了美国城市居民的生活节奏与仅仅半个世纪以前相比，发生了多大的变化。

yingyinNormal.en: These workers are employed in the largest urban area in the world, Guangdong Province in southern China where many of them live the entire year.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这些工人在世界上最大的城镇地区工作，中国南方的广东省，他们中很多人平时就在那里生活。

yingyinNormal.en: Outside the urban areas, visitors are often surprised to learn that over forty percent of the Hong Kong's territory has been designated as national park.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在市区，游客会对香港有超过四成地方获指定为公园感到惊讶。

yingyinNormal.en: It's one more system limited by plans made in another era. 100 years ago, most people in Los Angeles traveled by streetcar, and they had the largest urban rail network in the world.
yingyinNormal.zh: 受计划限制非常多的系统，100年前大多洛杉矶的人坐有轨电车出门，他们拥有世上最庞大的城市铁路网络。

yingyinNormal.en: Which suggests either a remarkable passivity among the, I assume, 24 to 36 residents of this building, based on the number of mailboxes and given typical urban population density or a shared delusion of functionality.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这就说明要么这楼的24到36户人家，我假设的，基于邮箱的个数和典型的城市人口密度得出的都特别懒散，要么都同时产生功能性错觉。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence_trans: 另一方面，波义耳家族则代表着其肮脏的城市面貌。
